<br>
I've done the stein of moggok quest many times with this.<br>
<br>
Not sure about Luminare tho... she could be picky.  She told me that I may now kiss her feet once I finished the illusion quest.<br>
<br>
BTW: This spell is for LOOKS ONLY!!!  Do not attempt to go into Cabilis under this illusion unless you are an Enchanter who follows Cazic Thule!!!  Cabilis faction is religion faction.  I made the misfortune of taking a forest giant to the trooper to save me.  Whoops.  You have been slain by Trooper Wetshispants.  Not fun.  Had to get a nice lizard to drag my corpse for me.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, and while its fun to look like an iksar in the EC tunnel, don't decide to go to a shopkeeper and buy stuff.  It won't work and you end up aggroing the guards that like to hang about in the commons. :)<br>
<br>
-Tremaile <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uretna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Retna</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(11/8/00 4:15:25 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/mysticalministry/ret.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Illusion Iksar quest</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the info, and it did work, he gave the powder in then I gave the other 3 components and I got the scroll.<br>
